  "instructions": [
    "In a large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the chopped onion and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the chopped carrot and celery and cook for 5 minutes, until tender.",
    "Add the rinsed lentils, dried thyme, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Pour in the red wine vinegar and water, and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.",
    "Let the stew cool to room temperature, then cover and refrigerate for at least 24 hours to allow fermentation.",
    "When ready to serve, stir in the Greek yogurt (if using) to add creaminess.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning as needed."
  ],
